  "text": "Considering these estimates as the known parameters, we generated 20 Phase II observations from a multivariate normal distribution with mean µ 1 and covariance matrixˆ 0 , such that the size of δ (in equation (7)) is approximately 0.087, which is a small shift in the mean vector. Specifically, we used, µ 1 = (21.12, 40.12, 15.29, 22.12, 26.11) . The inspiration for generating data in such manner is taken from [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] . The simulated bimetal Phase II data is given in Table 11 .",
